directions: Melt chocolate with coffee in saucepan over very low heat. Stir until melted and smooth.
Cool slightly.
Beat egg whites as for meringue.
When whites are in soft peaks, add sugar gradually. Continue beating until meringue is very stiff and you cannot feel or taste any grain of sugar.
Stir egg yolks into melted chocolate.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and butter.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend butter with flour and add to corn.
Mix well and remove from heat.

title: minestrone
directions: In a medium pot of lightly salted boiling water, cook the noodles until just tender, about 6 minutes.
Drain; rinse under cold water and drain again.
Set the noodles aside.
In a large pot, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add the onion, carrot, celery and garlic and cook, stirring occasionally until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the vegetable stock, tomatoes, potato, rosemary, basil, oregano, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to a simmer and cook, partially covered, until potatoes are almost tender, about 8 minutes.
Add noodles.
Simmer 1 minute before serving.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook Boston butt the day before (save broth).
Run pork and drained canned chicken through chopper.
Add all other ingredients, except potatoes.
We put potatoes in last to thicken. Yields 350 servings.

title: italian tomato meat sauce
directions: Set out a large saucepan with tight fitting lid.
Heat in saucepan 1/4 cup olive oil.
Add and cook until lightly browned 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Add and brown, turning occasionally, beef chuck and pork shoulder.
Add slowly a mixture of 7 cups tomatoes, sieved, 1 tablespoon salt and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 2 1/2 hours.
Add tomato paste.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, uncovered about 2 hours more, until thickened.
Before serving remove bay leaf and meat.

title: black bean dip
directions: Make ahead.
Beat 10 minutes in mixer.
Chill. Can be frozen.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Dissolve
jello in boiling water and Kool-Aid in water. Mix together; add sugar and pineapple juice.
Chill overnight. When ready
to
serve, add 7-Up and pineapple sherbet.
Serves approximately 30.

title: basting sauce (tomato)(good for venison.)
directions: Mix together and use as basting sauce.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt butter
and
cheese over low heat.
Sift cocoa and powdered sugar
and stir into melted mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered container and cool.
Mixture will be very thick.
Makes a lot.

title: oriental chicken
directions: In hot skillet or wok, saute onions, carrots and bell pepper in vegetable oil until turning soft.
If using a wok with a holding shelf, move vegetables up on shelf and use remaining oil to stir-fry chicken.

title: banana nut bread(recipe of gladys peterson)
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening well. Add eggs, one at a time. Add mashed bananas, then flour, soda and salt sifted 3 times together.
Add pecans and raisins and mix in well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
When brown, test with a straw for doneness. Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: turtles
directions: Remove	wrappers
from	caramels.
Soften
slightly
in microwave.	Flatten
caramel
pieces.
In a double boiler melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Stir.
Dip flattened caramel in chocolate to coat the bottom.
Lay	on wax paper.
Put 2 pecan halves on top of caramel.
Spoon melted chocolate on pecans to cover nuts and caramel.

title: favorite pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, soup, carrots, onion, sour cream and 2/3 of dressing mix.
Place in a buttered dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Before the last 10 minutes of cooking, combine remaining stuffing mix with butter and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: aunt rosie's grape salad
directions: Mix 5 ingredients together. Add grapes and stir. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: best ever lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until fluffy.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each one.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add small amounts of flour to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Add cold and boiling water, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Beat well, then gradually add remaining flour until well mixed.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Use as needed.
Butter muffin pan, shape and let rise in pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Rolls will keep up to two weeks.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Put hominy (I like yellow), butter, salt, pepper and grated sharp cheese in layers in heavy casserole.
Bake until cheese has melted and is bubbly.
You can layer as many times as you want. (Excellent for a cold winter night meal.)

title: golden punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot water; add jello, stirring well.
Add cold water, juices and extract.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Freeze some in ice trays or ring mold to float in punch bowl.
Slice lemons and limes for decoration.

title: cucumber and noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on box.
Combine sliced, peeled cucumbers (thin), chopped onion, pepper and tomato.
Add vinegar and mayonnaise in large bowl.
Add cooked noodles.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Add cheese and mix before serving.

title: honey glazed chicken
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Roll chicken in butter, then arrange in single layer pan.
Drizzle honey mixture over chicken. Baste 2 or 3 times; bake about 1 hour.

title: tropical punch
directions: Puree a soft, ripe banana in a blender.
Add the orange juice and pineapple juice and blend together.
Just before serving, add the lemon lime soda and mix well.
Put a spoonful of lemon sherbet in each glass and fill with punch.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: something different
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1/2 cup nuts together. Put in bottom of a pan.
Whip together the cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and pineapple, then put on top of graham cracker crumbs.

title: hot pepper lasagna
directions: *Regular lasagna may be used.
Sprinkle each layer with 1/2 to 1 teaspoon hot pepper flakes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Roll steak in 1/2 cup flour and (salt?).
Pan-fry onions, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.
Add steak and brown. Remove meat, onions and mushrooms from pan. Combine 2 tablespoons flour with drippings in the pan. Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thickened. Add sour cream and heat slowly until gravy simmers.
Add beef and vegetables and heat until hot. Serve hot on cooked rice, toast, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: potatoes au gratin(very delicious and so easy to prepare)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a baking sheet or dish with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices.

title: mushrooms in wine
directions: Brown mushrooms in a saucepan in vegetable oil with salt, thyme, pepper and bay leaf.
Add the wine.
Cover and cook over low heat about 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before cooking.

title: cookies 'n cream pie
directions: Pour milk into a large bowl.
Add pudding and beat with wire whisk until well blended (1 minute).
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and crushed cookies.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm (about 6 hours or overnight). Remove from freezer.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Store any leftovers in freezer.

title: chicken, artichoke and mushroom casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in 4 tablespoons butter and remove to a casserole which has a cover. Arrange artichoke hearts in between the chicken pieces.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In baking bowl, stir together the sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave for 3 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla to ingredients, mixing well.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add baking soda. Gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour the mixture on greased pan.

title: golden baked onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Melt 1 stick margarine in a large pot. Add all sliced onions. Saute until onions are soft and transparent. Do not overcook. Using a slotted spoon, transfer onions to a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish (I use Pyrex).
Mix together the soup, milk and pepper until smooth. Pour over the onions. Top with grated cheese.
Melt remaining stick of margarine.
Dip one side of sliced bread in margarine.
Put on top of casserole, buttered side up.
Continue with remaining bread slices, covering casserole completely and overlapping bread slices.
Bake,
uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes or until bread is golden brown. Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add potatoes, onion and tomato sauce.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and hot pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender and soup has thickened.

title: (dutch) drop cookies
directions: Mix well and drop from teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: grasshopper salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.
Chill thoroughly - best if made the night before serving.

title: glorious pie
directions: Mix all the above and pour into two graham cracker pie shells.
Let set 3 hours.
In refrigerator before servings.

title: "potato kugeli"
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into well-greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger beef stroganoff
directions: Cook onion and garlic in butter until transparent on medium heat.
Add meat.
Cook and stir until color is gone.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and stir in well.
Add sour cream.
Stir and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Garnish with paprika if you so desire. Leftovers are excellent over toast.

title: szechwan chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Dredge chicken in cornstarch.
Heat oil in wok or heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic and stir-fry until chicken is opaque, about 5 minutes.
Add soy mixture and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Mix in green onions.
Serve immediately with rice.

title: oatmeal pie - 9-inch
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: barbeque hamburg
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and celery,
Add chili sauce, ketchup, mustard, and butter.
Salt and pepper to taste and dab of open pit.

title: double duty lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown sausage, ground meat and garlic.
Drain excess grease.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Mix cottage cheese with egg and parsley.
Layer 1/2 noodles in two 8 x 8-inch baking dishes; spread with 1/2 cottage cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 meat sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 (2 2/3 x 2 2/3-inch) servings.

title: special chicken stuffing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and toss until moist.
Put half mixture in bottom of 15 x 18-inch greased pan.
Mix next 5 ingredients and set aside.
Put chicken mixture over stuffing, then top with remaining stuffing.
Beat 3 eggs and 1 1/2 cups milk. Pour over mixture in pan and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Add chicken or mushroom soup (diluted with 1 can water or 2 cups chicken broth).
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.
Remove and grate mild or sharp cheese over top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a medium cast-iron skillet on top of the stove and add brown sugar.
Make sure it is spread evenly in the bottom. Drain pineapple and arrange pineapple in skillet. Put a cherry in the center of each pineapple.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add to flour mixture.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan; cut in bars.

title: veal on green rice
directions: Cut veal into serving size pieces.
In shallow pan, combine garlic and next 5 ingredients.
Add meat and turn to cook well. Refrigerate and let stand for 5 or 6 hours.

title: blond fudge
directions: Butter sides of a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Combine sugar, milk and salt in pan.
Heat and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring only if necessary.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla. Beat vigorously until mixture begins to hold shape. Add Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until fudge becomes thick and loses its gloss. Quickly stir in cherries and spread in buttered shallow pan or small platter. Score in squares while warm.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk in a heavy saucepan.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Spread inside of a greased pan and chill 2 to 3 hours or until fudge is firm.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Cover the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with refried beans.
Mix the taco seasoning with sour cream.
Spread over the refried beans.
Layer, in order, the next 4 ingredients.
Then, top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fried corn, tennessee-style
directions: Preparation Time:
20 minutes.
Cooking Time:
15 minutes for rice and 10 minutes for beans.

title: mama's baked sweet potatoes
directions: You will need foil paper.

title: make-ahead chicken casserole
directions: Marinate chicken in eggs for 2 hours in the refrigerator. Combine bread crumbs, parsley, salt and garlic powder in plastic bag.
Shake chicken in bread crumb mixture and brown in oil. Drain and place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with sliced mushrooms and top with cheese slices.
Pour broth on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be made up ahead of time but pour broth on just before baking.

title: wedding cake icing
directions: For decorating, add desired food color.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and pudding and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar over batter.
Sprinkle nuts over sugar.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Pick over peas or beans and discard any stones.
Place in colander and rinse thoroughly.
Soak in water to cover overnight. Drain; rinse again.
Place in saucepan and cover with fresh cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, covered, until peas or beans are tender, but not mushy, about 1 hour.
Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking liquid.
Combine garlic, onion, parsley, mint, lemon juice, oil, reserved cooking liquid and salt, if used, in wide bowl.
Add drained peas or beans; toss well and chill. May be refrigerated one or two days to allow flavors to blend. Adjust seasoning.
Garnish with red onion.
Makes 8 servings.

title: big mac sauce(for hamburgs)
directions: Stir ingredients together (best if prepared the night before). Serve on hamburgs (on rolls) with chopped lettuce, sliced tomato, sliced onions and pickles.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk; mix thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix well.
Alternate graham crackers and pudding mixture.
Make three layers.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: dirty rice
directions: Chop livers onions, green pepper and celery.
Cook beef, liver, shrimp, pepper, onions and celery in salad oil until tender, but do not brown.
Stir in rice and beef bouillon.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: fish chowder
directions: In a large soup kettle/pan, saute onion 3 or more minutes. Add clam juice and juice from the potatoes.
Add diced fish. Cook 15 minutes on medium-high until fish is mostly done. Add potatoes and turn heat down to medium-low.

title: marinated pork loin roast
directions: Place roast in large plastic bag.
Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour over meat.
Press out air and close tight.
Marinate overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove roast and reserve marinade.
Place roast on rack in shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes per pound.
Last 1/2 hour of cooking, baste with marinade every 10 minutes.
Heat and serve marinade.

title: christmas cutout sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Next, add and cut butter into mixture with a mixer until fine.
Finally add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until very lightly browned.
Watch closely, cookies tend to burn easily.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Boil milk and butter.

title: praline brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
For praline layer, mix 2 eggs, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add in coconut and pecans. Mix well.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix up all and roll into meatballs.
Brown in oven on double broiler 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute onions in margarine; add green chilies.
Thicken with flour; stir until smooth.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place chicken pieces in dish and layer with noodles and cottage cheese; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, Velveeta cheese and 1/2 of the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with more Velveeta cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes a large casserole.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Drain spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix all together. Best when made night before using.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook hamburger and drain off grease. In another skillet, cook zucchini and onion in oleo until tender (10 to 20 minutes).
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In bowl, beat eggs and add cheese.
Spread a 9-inch crust with mustard. Pour vegetable and hamburger mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cover with foil last 10 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Spread over bottom of casserole dish.
Add soup and spread cooked potatoes over top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of potatoes.
Bake in oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sally's spicy fruit salad
directions: Add to "Spicy Cherry Sauce for Ham" recipe.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat sugar, eggs and oil.
Stir in strawberries and add flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour in bread pans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oreo dirt dessert
directions: Mix together and chill, milk and pudding mix. Separate the filling of the cookies. Crush the cookies and set aside. Mix together chilled pudding, cookie middles, cream cheese and Cool Whip. Starting with cookie crumbs, layer in a 9 x 13 pan. Chill and serve.

title: herbed mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in sterilized jars and store in a cool, dark place.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Unthaw broccoli and combine with Cheez Whiz.
Add soup, eggs, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
Put in large casserole dish and top with a few cracker crumbs and butter.
Cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crock-pot pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat. Spray large skillet with cooking spray. Add meat and brown meat on all sides. Place potatoes, mushrooms, carrots and basil in a 3 1/2 to 4-quart crock-pot. Place browned meat on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with salt. Pour condensed soup over meat. Cover and cook on low setting for 10 to 12 hours. Transfer meat and vegetables to serving platter. Serve the sauce over meat and vegetables. Yield: about 5 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream yolks with sugar.
Beat egg whites and fold in with other ingredients.
Add sugar and yolks (creamed).
Add 1 cup ground walnuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 12 pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Trim all visible fat from chicken.
Season chicken parts with pepper.
Combine flour and paprika in medium bowl.
Coat seasoned chicken with flour mixture.
Spray a 13 X 9 inch pan with vegetable spray.
Place chicken pieces, skin side down, in pan. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees until done.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix
together.
Bake
in an unbaked shell at 350° until it is crisp, approximately 1 hour.
Yield: One pie.

title: chili con carne
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion with garlic and cumin until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups.

title: 6 week cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and cover with salt. Let sit 2 hours. Add green pepper, celery, mustard seed, celery seed.	Boil sugar, vinegar and water.	Cool and pour over salad. Refrigerate for 2 to 6 weeks.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put liquids in blender and mix. Add dry ingredients and blend. Mix until thick.

title: creamy baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add scalded milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Flavor with vanilla and nutmeg.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Place in a shallow pan of warm water.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° to 350° for 40 minutes.
A knife inserted will come out clean when custard is done.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts and small onion.
When finished, remove the skin from the bone and chop up the meat; get rid of the skin. Add rest of ingredients.
Add orzo last and cook until tender.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, arrange ingredients in the following order:
pineapple with juice, blueberries, sugar, dry cake mix and melted margarine.
Sprinkle a small amount of sugar over the top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter; put in eggs and milk.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in pie crust.

title: aaron's molded salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk until very hot on stove.
Be careful not to burn!
Pour mixture over dry Jell-O and mix with mixer until blended.
Blend all other ingredients.
Pour into dish and let set. May be used as a salad or dessert.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain fat.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kay's bean soup
directions: Brown all sides of meat in shortening.
Add next 3 ingredients and simmer over low heat for about an hour or until meat falls from bone.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until potatoes are done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: creme puff rolls
directions: Stir butter, water, salt and flour until it leaves the spoon. Take off and cool 10 minutes.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat them in well. Roll out 1/2 tablespoon at a time.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add mustard, brown sugar, ketchup and pork and beans.
Simmer 5 minutes on low heat.
Serve over buns or bread.

title: scott's favorite spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Cook onion and minced garlic in oil until tender.
Do not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, then remove bay leaf.
Add meatballs.
Cover loosely and cook 30 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti with Parmesan cheese.

title: old fashioned chocolate pie
directions: Heat egg yolks, milk and butter.
Mix together dry ingredients and pour into heated liquid.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in a 325° oven.

title: paprika chicken
directions: In skillet, melt margarine; brown chicken about 10 minutes. Remove and set aside.
Spoon off fat.

title: dinner rolls(mrs. tetterton)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Add milk, butter, salt, remaining sugar, eggs and 3 cups of flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes, adding additional flour as needed.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down. Turn out on lightly floured surface; divide in half.
Divide each half into 12 pieces.
Shape in balls.
Place in 2 greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Brush with melted butter.
Yields 2 dozen large rolls.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, puddings and cooking oil.
Blend together and then beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat another minute.
Stir in chocolate chips; pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini.
Cut off stems.
Drop in boiling, salted water. Cover.
Turn heat on low and cook for 10 minutes or less.
Cool. Cut in half lengthwise.
Remove pulp and chop.
Cook spinach. Drain and squeeze dry.
Combine flour, milk, zucchini pulp and spinach.

title: fluffy salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese,
Cool Whip and dry Jell-O.	Add all fruits.
Mix!

title: almond butter crunch
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar, syrup and water. Cook, stirring constantly, to hard crack (300°).
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped almonds.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch metal pan (no glass).
Cool thoroughly; turn onto waxed paper. Spread with 1/2 melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with 1/2 chopped almonds.
Cover with wax paper; turn over and spread with rest of chocolate and sprinkle with nuts.
Break into pieces after chocolate hardens.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar and 1 cup vinegar.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables and keep in fridge.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large pan and put in oven preheated to 400° until topping is prepared.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spoon over apples and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Pour berries into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar, milk and margarine together.
Pour over berries; will have the texture of cake batter.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar and cornstarch.
Sprinkle mixture on top of batter.
Pour boiling water over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: party cake
directions: Grease sides of two 8-inch layer pans.
Line bottom of each pan with waxed paper dusted with flour.
Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder into a large mixing bowl.
Add the shortening and 1/2 cup milk; beat 2 minutes on low speed of mixer. Add remaining milk, vanilla and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes. Bake in a moderate 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: moo-goo gai pan
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Heat oil and saute meat until it turns white (3 to 4 minutes). Push aside; add almonds.
Stir until brown.
Add scallions, mushrooms, green peppers and ginger.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add peas; cook 2 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in some of broth.
Add remaining broth, sherry and soy sauce; add to chicken mixture. Cook until sauce is smooth and shiny, about 4 minutes longer. (Beef bouillon can be substituted for chicken broth.)

title: orange-glazed chicken oriental
directions: Whisk the first 5 ingredients in small bowl until cornstarch and honey dissolve.

Heat oil in large heavy skillet over high heat. Add onion, garlic and orange peel and stir-fry until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add chicken and stir-fry until opaque, about 3 minutes. Stir orange juice mixture. Add to skillet and stir-fry until chicken is cooked through and liquid thickens, about 4 minutes. Season with freshly ground pepper and salt, if desired.
Serve with rice (and, if desired, thinly sliced green part of onion remaining).

title: rhubarb slush
directions: Simmer rhubarb and water for 15 minutes. Drain, keep juice. Add sugar, jello and lemonade. Stir well. Add one cup vodka and freeze. Serve with cup or strawberry pop.

title: broken glass torte
directions: Use 1 1/4 cups water to each box of jello.
Put in separate pans.
Cut in small squares when completely set.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Blend eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Brown sausage and cube.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch glass pan (or 2-quart casserole). Make 3 layers:
bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour well mixed egg mixture over top (add more milk to cover bread).
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham and pea soup
directions: Boil moderately fast for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally to prevent scorching.

title: pizza swiss
directions: Combine the flour, salt and pepper and pound into steak.
Brown slowly on both sides in hot fat.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over meat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Place in baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate coconut candies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Roll into balls.
Let dry a while, then roll again.
Make the balls look nice, then dip into dipping chocolate. I use part dipping chocolate and mix a few chocolate into it and a little paraffin.

title: light lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl; add vegetable oil and next 4 ingredients. Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer 6 minutes. Stir in poppy seeds. Pour batter into a 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pan; drizzle with Lemon Glaze and cool completely on wire rack. Yield: 24 servings (156 cal--27% from fat per slice. 2.8g protein, 4.7g fat (1.1g saturated), 25.6g carbohydrate, 0.1g fiber, 0.2mg cholesterol, 168mg sodium and 44mg calcium.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Combine apples, bananas, celery, walnuts and coconut.

title: reese cup
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter and graham crackers; mix well.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate.
Melt paraffin and chocolate together.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Set on waxed paper to cool.
Makes 100 pieces.

title: beef casserole
directions: Set chips and cheese aside.
Mix all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and top with chips and cheese; return to oven and cook until cheese is melted.

title: capon stuffing
directions: Brown chopped onions and rice in margarine.
Add water, bouillon, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Salt cavity of capon and stuff.

title: squash casserole
directions: Alternate layers (squash, onion and dressing).
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cook lemon jello in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip and sugar together real good.
Add cooled lemon mixture. Pour over a graham cracker crust.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions; cover with boiling water.
Drain immediately.
Cover with cold water; bring to boil.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Put in hot, sterile jars and seal.
No processing necessary.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken noodle supreme
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° F. for 25 minutes. Easy but tasty.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, pecans and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread topping at once over warm cake.
Let cool. Frost.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Roll into ball the size of walnut.
Roll into mixture of 1/4 cup cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Bake until brown and still soft 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add sugar, salt, oil and egg.
Add flour gradually, beating well after each addition.
Grease the top with oil and let rise until doubled in size.
Pour on floured board and knead.
Shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put 1 stick margarine in a baking dish. Put in oven and allow margarine to melt.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan lightly with cooking spray.
Melt margarine and pour into pan.
Add other ingredients in layers as listed.
Press lightly the first 6 ingredients before adding Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool overnight before cutting into small pieces.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar. Add to mixture.
Mix in vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with glass or spoon to flatten.
Sprinkle tops of cookies with sugar. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry yogurt shake
directions: In a blender, mix all ingredients until smooth.
(Or use frozen berries, skim milk and sweetener for a lo-cal shake.)

title: coconut torte
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and add sugar; beat until stiff. Add crumbs and rest of ingredients.
Bake in a large pie tin or cake pan at 350° until done or golden, about 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: reunion cake pie
directions: Make pie layer:
Into medium bowl, combine corn syrup, pecans, eggs, vanilla, sugar, dash of salt and 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour pecan mixture into lightly greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a preheated 400°
oven for 15 minutes.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Combine all together.
Bake at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicken broth
directions: Wash and cut hen into frying pieces.
Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in large saucepan and cover with water.
Cook on stovetop until meat is done, about 1 hour (45 minutes in pressure cooker).
Remove chicken from pot, discard celery and carrots; strain broth.
Reserve chicken for other uses.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine catsup, cracker crumbs and milk; let stand 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake on flat pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: Cook bacon; reserve 2 tablespoons fat.	Cook vegetables at low temperature for about 1 hour.
Add bacon and fat.

title: dill beans
directions: Mix oleo and flour.
Add liquid, milk and cheese.
Pour over beans and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hurry up hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add both cans of soup and half of the noodles.
Put in casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining noodles and bake 10 more minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook and drain sliced carrots.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Mix vegetables with soup and dash of pepper and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with croutons mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate.
Thaw broccoli and drain well.
Mix broccoli, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 1 minute on high speed.
Pour over ingredients in pie pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pan comes out clean.

title: tex-mex spice mix
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly and store in an airtight container for up to 3 months.

title: fruited chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, spreading fruit and onions on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: tapenade(an olive-based appetizer spread from the sunny south of france.)
directions: Mash the olives in a large bowl (they will look like crushed cockroaches), adding olive oil as necessary to make a thick paste. Chill.
Serve in a shallow glass bowl decorated with parsley. Put the bowl on a tray and surround it with crusty French bread or pita triangles.
Serves 8 people.

title: chocolate candy bar dessert
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, 1/4 c. sugar and melted margarine in 9x13" pan.
Press firmly into bottom of pan.
Refrigerate 10 min.
Beat cream cheese & remaining 1/4 c. sugar until smooth.
Gently stir in half the whipped topping.
Spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle candy bars over cream cheese.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding.
Beat with a wire whisk for 1 min.
Pour over candy bar layer.
Let stand 5 min., until thickened.
Spread remaining whipped topping over pudding layer.
Refrigerate 2 hrs. or until set.
Garnish with additional chopped candy bars if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all together and bring to a boil.
Brush on chicken as you barbecue.
Makes enough for 10 halves.
Will keep in refrigerator.

title: russian cream(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Combine half and half, sugar and gelatin in 2-quart saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved; cool to lukewarm.
Whisk in sour cream, vanilla and almond extract until mixture is smooth.
Pour into 6-cup metal mold.
Refrigerate, covered, until set, at least 4 hours.
To unmold, dip mold into warm water just until edges begin to liquify.
Invert onto serving platter; surround with well drained Marinated Strawberries.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together; add zucchini. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder; add to zucchini mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves. Nuts and raisins are optional.

title: quick cucumber slices
directions: Place cucumbers, onions and salt in a bowl; cover with ice cubes and let stand together for 1 to 3 hours; drain well.
Mix until dissolved, sugar, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over drained cukes.
Place in jar, cover and refrigerate.

title: marvelous mushroom gravy
directions: Cook coarsely chopped mushrooms in water and salt for 20 minutes.
Add onions; simmer 3 minutes.
Sprinkle in garlic powder; add salt and pepper to mix.
Drain mixture; save stock.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Sift dry ingredients and work in butter.
Cover bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan and press firmly.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix fruit juices, sugar, salt, eggs and butter together and cook until thick and add to macaroni. Cool.
Next morning, add drained fruit and large carton of Cool Whip.

title: german cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in boiling, salted water and boil for 5 minutes.
Fry bacon pieces slowly until brown.
Drain cabbage thoroughly.
Mix onions and bell pepper with cabbage in bowl.
Add bacon bits and drippings to cabbage.
Add 1 tablespoon salad dressing or mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: blueberry-nectarine crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Toss nectarines, blueberries, granulated sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch in large bowl. Spoon fruit mixture into 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish. Mix flour and brown sugar. Mix butter into flour mixture until crumbly. Sprinkle over top of fruit. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add evaporated milk and dry soup mix.
Stir until well mixed.
Set aside.
Mix beef and pork in large bowl.
Add raw onion, if desired.

Combine the liquid mixture with meats and blend well, using hands works best. Add cracker crumbs until mixture can be handled to form loaf. Spread remaining crumbs on wax paper and roll meat loaf in crumbs. Place in sprayed pan.
Cover bottom of pan with water around loaf.
Bake, covered, at 350° until heated through.
Add water, if necessary.
Uncover after 30 to 35 minutes.
Add water, if necessary, and finish baking until done.
Do not allow pan to get dry during baking.
Top should brown nicely while finishing.
Oven temperature may be adjusted according to need.
Yields 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: soft jumble cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt three times.
Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and milk. Bake at 350° to 375°.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Put oil into deep frypan; add beef.
Fry until browned.
Add onion, green pepper and brown gravy mix.
Cover and cook until meat is tender.

title: riviera bean salad
directions: Drain bean salad and tuna.
Mix well.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: frosted strawberry squares
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, walnuts and oleo.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Check often and stir occasionally.
Cool.

title: corn bread sticks
directions: Beat egg, sugar and shortening together.
Sift flour and meal together with salt and baking powder, then gradually add to other mixture, alternating with the clabber.
Pour into iron cornstick pans and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: hot broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Cube cheese.
Drain mushrooms.
Chop onions. Dice garlic very small.
In frying pan, melt butter.
Fry onions and garlic.
In large bowl, mix broccoli, cheese, mushrooms and onions.
Beat in 2 eggs; mix well.
Grease casserole dish and add mixture and smooth top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top until covered.
Lay 6 to 8 pats of butter on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(When butter is melted and mixture bubbles, casserole is done.)

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together ground beef, spaghetti sauce, spaghetti mix, and oregano.
In a large baking dish, layer noodles, meat sauce mixture, parmesan cheese, noodles, mozzarella cheese, meat sauce mixture, noodles, and top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: Brown beef with the shortening in a large skillet.
Stir with a fork to break up meat.
Add soup mix, water, ketchup, mustard, vinegar, pork and beans and kidney beans.
Mix well.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Can be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Heat all ingredients until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove bacon.
Reserve pan drippings in skillet.
Set bacon aside to drain.
Saut garlic, onion and mushrooms
in skillet until tender.
Stir in bacon, flour and seasoned salt.
Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Place half of slices in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon half of bacon mixture over tomatoes; sprinkle with 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In a large pan saute the onion; add celery, potatoes, fish, shrimp, scallops and lemon juice.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Add the onion salt, parsley, basil and dill weed.

title: german rolled beef
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizers on each side and pound.
Spread mustard thinly over meat; season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle chopped onion and pickle over each piece and place bacon over each piece.
Roll up and fasten with toothpicks.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Add 1/2 cup water and simmer 1 hour or until tender.
Use flour to make a paste to thicken gravy.
Serve over meat.

title: hot pepper vinegar
directions: Place peppers in a glass container.
Bring vinegar to a boil and pour over peppers. Put on a loose lid and let stand 1 week. Remove peppers and use vinegar as a condiment for French fries, fish, chile or whatever.

title: fideo soup
directions: Put about 1/4-inch oil in pot over low heat. Add slightly crushed fideo.
Cook until light brown. Turn off heat. Drain oil. Add garlic, onion and tomato sauce. Stir quickly. Add boiling water and bouillon cubes.
Return to a boil. Cover and lower heat to a simmer. Cook about 7 to 8 minutes or until noodles are done.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix sugar and butter together with mixer on medium speed.
Add 1 egg at a time to mixture.
Add whipping cream, then flour.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss cheese fondue
directions: Toss cheese and flour in bowl.
Heat wine and garlic in electric fondue pot just until bubbles form.
Remove and discard garlic.
Add cheese to the wine, a handful at a time, stirring with wooden spoon until each addition is blended.
Stir in Kirsch and nutmeg.
Keep fondue warm on low setting during dipping.

title: pansy pound cake
directions: You do not use baking powder in this cake.
Don't use self-rising flour.
Cream mixture until smooth.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal-brown sugar pancakes
directions: Beat egg; add milk and oil, mixing well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Add egg mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir oats into batter.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Makes 10 pancakes.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, Italian seasoning and sugar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of uncooked lasagne noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese, and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.

title: cheese rice broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli as directed on package.
Blend all ingredients together in a Pyrex dish and sprinkle top with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Beat in molasses and egg.
Mix well.
Add coconut and nuts; mix well. Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 30 cookies.

title: smash cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1 of the eggs, the butter and pecans.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.

title: braided carrot bread
directions: Over low heat, heat milk, water and oleo until hot (125°). Stir into flour mixture (flour, carrots, wheat germ, sugar, salt, savory and yeast).
Mix to form soft dough; let rise 10 minutes. Divide into 3 pieces.
Roll into 15-inch ropes.
Braid together. Place on baking sheet and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: quickie calzone
directions: Roll out dough and put cheese and sausage on top; fold in half and pinch down edges to seal. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone and tear chicken into small pieces.
Mix first three ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole dish suitable for oven baking.
Then mix separately last three ingredients and spread on top of chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes or until the casserole is bubbling around the edges.

title: german slaw
directions: Boil all the ingredients 15 minutes except cabbage and onion. Remove spice bag.
Let mixture cool 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugars, butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange cooler
directions: Dissolve Jell-O into boiling water.
Add cranberry juice. Pour over ice cubes in tall glasses and garnish with orange slices.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 4 servings.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Top with layer of coconut and top with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate and chill for at least 4 hours.

title: rhubarb strawberry coffee cake
directions: In bowl, mix together the dry ingredients; cut in butter.
Mix buttermilk, eggs and vanilla add to dry mix.
Stir to moisten. Spread half the batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread cooled filling over batter in pan.
Spoon remaining batter in small mounds on top of filling.
Combine remaining sugar and flour; cut in butter.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown beef and drain.
Brown onion and green pepper.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 1 hour.

title: venison salami
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate mixture for three days, taking it out to remix at least once a day.
On the 4th day, shape the mixture into small loaves about 2 1/2 x 6-inches long. Put on cookie sheet and bake overnight or 10 hours at 150°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken. Season to taste. Butter casserole dish. Put in chicken in small serving pieces.
Add the soups, chicken broth and stuffing mix over all.
Dot with butter. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: yellow punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Drain vegetables after chopping.
Beat together cheese and lemon juice.
Stir in vegetables.
Great on crackers or in sandwiches.

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Add the chili powder, garlic powder and sugar to the browned and drained hamburger and onion.
After mixing that, add the tomato sauce and beans and sauce.
Put mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread prepared cornbread (uncooked) over the top. Follow instructions on cornbread for cooking.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine sour cream and milk, stirring well.
In large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until light and fluffy.
At low speed, blend in flour and sour cream mixture, alternating, beginning and ending with flour.
Then blend in melted butter. Use 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring the sugar and vinegar to a boil; cook until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and mix all ingredients together.
Put in a quart jar and let marinate all night in the refrigerator.
Turn jar each day to mix.
This will keep for several weeks.

title: balsamic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Combine vinegar and garlic in small saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil. Continue to boil until thick and syrupy, about 8 minutes. Stir in rosemary. Season chicken with salt and pepper and place in a large heavy skillet, skin side down and sear until brown, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove chicken and pour off excess fat. Return chicken to pan, skin side up. Place in oven and roast 10 to 15 minutes. Remove chicken from oven and turn on broiler. Brush chicken with reduced balsamic mixture. Place under broiler until glaze is bubbly, 1 to 3 minutes.

title: elegant peach delight
directions: Combine cake mix and softened margarine and press in lightly greased 12 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange peaches on top.
Beat sour cream and egg yolks together and pour over peaches, spreading to sides of pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: wakefield dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayo.
Mix in lemon juice, chopped onions, mustard and garlic salt. Fold in broken up crabmeat. Chill several hours (will thicken). Serve in carved out red cabbage with assorted crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Put cheese in a crock-pot on medium heat until melted.
Add tomatoes and sausage.
Serve.
Pour over tortilla chips or as a dip.

title: fasta pasta - 10 minute pasta sauce
directions: In a heavy skillet, add oil, fresh tomatoes and 1/4 of wine. Saute until the tomatoes cook down until soft and tender.
Add garlic, onion, basil and can of cooked tomatoes and rest of wine. Cook on high for 2 minutes, then cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Pour over your choice of pasta and add Parmesan cheese.

title: old fashioned egg pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour in a 9-inch unbaked shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is set.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
(Do not overboil, just to a boil.)
Add peanut butter and vanilla to mixture and blend smooth, then add Rice Krispies and mix.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Just mix well; do not beat.
Bake at 350° 75 minutes.

title: meal in one(serving size: 6)
directions: Place Tater Tots on bottom and up side of 8 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown and drain beef.
Place beef, broccoli and 1/2 can onions on potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen rolls in pan. Mix brown sugar and pudding mix; sprinkle over rolls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over brown sugar-pudding mixture.
Spread pecans over this and pour melted butter over pecans.
Place on cabinet overnight; do not cover.
In morning, bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let sit in pan 10 to 15 minutes, then turn out. Slice or pull apart.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Cap, clean and wash peppers; grind peppers.
Drain.
Grind onions.
Prepare big pot of boiling water.
Put onions and peppers together and cover with boiling water for 10 minutes.
Put 3 trays ice on until melted.
Drain well.
Put in big pot and add all ingredients except pickling spices.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and let float in pickle while it cooks.
Boil about 30 minutes.
Jar and seal.
Makes 9 quarts.

title: frozen strawberries
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar together.
Let stand 20 minutes. Combine pectin and water and boil 1 minute.
Pour over berries. Mix well.
Seal in freezer containers and freeze.
Makes 5 pints.

title: roadside potatoes
directions: Put potatoes through medium food grinder or food processor; don't overprocess.
Mix together the potatoes, green peppers, onion, cheese and flour.
Add melted butter, salt and pepper. Pour into greased casserole.
Pour warm milk over top and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, vegetable oil and sugar.
Add zucchini. Mix well in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add flour, baking soda, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: lemonade dessert
directions: Use a prepared crust for pie or make one up yourself with graham crackers and margarine; add 1/4 cup sugar.
May be pressed down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip Eagle Brand and lemonade.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared crust, then refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: ranch style casserole(mexican food)
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in a little oil. Add Ro-Tel, mushroom soup, Ranch Style beans, salt and pepper.
Mix well and heat about 5 minutes.
In a large casserole, layer meat mixture, torn tortillas and grated cheese. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except broccoli and bread crumbs. Add broccoli and mix.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to hour, or until golden brown on top.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: polynesian carrot frappe
directions: In a blender or food processor, whirl the pineapple juice and carrots until smooth.
Add the ice cream; whirl to blend.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sour cream until foamy.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in egg mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: persimmon nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Dust raisins and nuts with a little flour; add all dry ingredients, raisins and nuts to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen orange juice until completely dissolved.
Add drained orange sections and crushed pineapple.
Freeze until set, about two hours. One hour before serving, combine lemon instant pudding mix with one cup cold milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread evenly onto gelatin and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 12 -15 Use 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish.

title: texas cookie sheet cake
directions: Combine the flour and sugar. Boil the oleo, cocoa, oil and Coke.
Pour over the flour mixture. Add the salt, buttermilk, eggs, vanilla, soda and cinnamon.
Mix together and pour in well oiled pan. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat. Stir in apples and pecans.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: bounce back cocktail
directions: Puree all ingredients on high in blender until smooth and frothy.

title: mexican hogies
directions: Brown ground chuck;
add
onion,
bell pepper and salt; drain. Add
remaining
ingredients.
Let	cheese	melt,
then cool. Fill hogie	buns
(or
hot	dog buns) and wrap in foil. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 400°.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: cucumber salad mold
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Cool at room temperature.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into Jello mixture.
Pour into salad mold.
Chill until firm.
(Serves 6-8.)

title: cajun cole slaw
directions: Slice cabbage.
Mix all ingredients together and add to the cabbage.
Thin the mayonnaise with the beaten egg white and add to the slaw.
(A little vinegar and/or sugar may be added according to your personal taste.)

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spoon into sprayed muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mary's irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, sugar, salt, currants, raisins and caraway seed.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat with a fork and stir into dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 2 large loaf cakes.

title: hawaiian holiday punch
directions: Mix all together and serve. Can make ice ring using punch, orange slices and maraschino cherries.

title: fruit cake
directions: Prepare molding pans by putting waxed paper in them so that the ends of paper are above pans.
Cut all fruit into smaller pieces. Crumble Ritz crackers.
Chop nuts.
Mix all ingredients except milk and marshmallows well.
Heat water and stir in marshmallows to melt them.
Then add dry milk and remove from heat.
Pour over the other ingredients and mix well.
Press cake mixture tightly into round angel food cake pan or small loaf pans.
Allow to dry overnight. Remove from pan(s) and allow to air dry a few more hours or a day with bottom end(s) turned up.
This can be frozen then.

title: spinach squares
directions: Wash, cook and drain spinach.
Beat eggs.
Add butter, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cheese, onion, spinach and mushrooms.
Put mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and level mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 45 minutes.
Cut into bite size squares.

title: golden lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Saute onions and green pepper in butter.
Add mushrooms, soup, milk and basil;
mix
well.	Layer
noodles,
cheeses, chicken and sauce one-half at a time in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving. This	is
an excellent	dish
to
freeze;
simply remove from freezer and place directly in oven.
No need to thaw first.

title: sausage wrapped in pastry
directions: Combine flour, fennel and salt in bowl.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cut butter and shortening into pieces and add to flour.
Use pastry cutter to cut to coarse texture.
Add ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time, and toss with fork until mixture forms a ball.
Makes 2 balls.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill for 30 minutes.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Wash green tomatoes and chop in food processor, enough to make 2 cups. Boil sugar and chopped tomatoes 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add jello; dissolve. Put into hot jelly glasses. Put 1/8 inch paraffin on top. Tastes like raspberry jam.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt caramels, milk and margarine in double boiler.
Remove and add pecans and vanilla.
Drop on buttered wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Dip in chocolate and paraffin melted together. Chill again on wax paper.
Enjoy!

title: scripture cake
directions: After following instructions in Proverbs 23:14, pour batter into well-greased loaf pans and bake 50 minutes in preheated oven. Cool and slice after a few John 11:9.

title: picante pesto pasta
directions: Combine spinach, Pace picante, cheese, pecans, oil and garlic in blender or food processor and process until smooth.
Toss spinach mixture with hot cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with additional chopped pecans.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sticky buns
directions: Bring syrup, margarine, nuts and cinnamon to a boil.
Cook and stir about 30 seconds.
Pour into small baking pan.
Arrange biscuits in pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Invert at once onto a serving plate.
(Please be very careful; this is a hot sugar syrup mixture and you can get a severe burn if it drops on your fingers.)
If you don't want to invert it, have an adult do it for you.
Yields 10.
Be careful; be safety conscious!

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Cut wieners into bite size pieces.
Heat sauce and wieners thoroughly in crock-pot or saucepan on low.
Serve warm from dish or on toothpicks.
Excess sauce can be refrigerated and reused.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Peel and cut apples into bite size pieces; add next 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over apple mixture and mix well.

title: potato soup
directions: Put the potatoes, soup and onion in covered casserole dish. Microwave for 16 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Add the remaining ingredients to the potato mixture.
Put all in crock-pot and heat.

title: orange-glazed ham
directions: Place ham on
a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Stud ham with cloves, if desired.
Combine orange juice concentrate, brown sugar and mustard.
Brush on ham.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes to 1 hour or until thermometer registers 140°, basting occasionally.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: little burgers
directions: Mix together mustard, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and onions.
Slice rolls in half.
Spread mustard sauce on bottom layer.
Top with ham slices.
Top ham with cheese.
Replace top of rolls.
Place back into foil pan.
Slice in 12 sandwiches.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated and cheese melts.

title: florabell rominger's blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together shortening, 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix berries, 1 cup sugar and boiling water.
Pour over batter mixture to cover.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and mix well.
Mix rice, onion, butter and oil in 1 cup of hot water.
Cook rice mixture approximately 15 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Put everything in a large pot.
Cook slowly until tender. Wash and scald 9 pint jars and lids.
When vegetables are tender, put in jars and seal while hot.
Makes 9 pints.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Add melted stick of butter.
Pour on extra cup of stuffing on top after mixing or crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Skin and slice 6 large, ripe and firm tomatoes.
Slice 1 large green pepper into strips; slice 1 red onion into rings.
Place in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cucumber.
Place over heat; bring to boil.
Boil furiously only 1 minute.
Pour over tomatoes while hot.
Cool.
Just before serving, add 1 peeled and sliced cucumber.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Mix Ricotta cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread evenly on top of cake batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour in oblong pan.

title: chicken spaghetti 2
directions: In a medium-sized skillet or saucepan, lightly saute the onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms; set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add water to cover beans (about 7 cups).
Cook about 8 hours on high in crock-pot.

title: butternut squash cake
directions: In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Beat eggs. Add to spice mixture. Mix dry ingredients together. Slowly add to spice mixture. Beat 5 minutes. Add pineapple, squash and nuts. Fold in. Pour in large, greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 55 minutes. Cool. Frost with Buttercream Frosting or your favorite frosting.

title: hawaiian cooler
directions: Prepare frozen juices as labels direct.
Pour over ice in a large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale.
Top with pineapple chunks and cherries.

title: deviled ham tea sandwiches
directions: Mix all together. Make sandwiches. Cut off crust, then cut as desired.

title: family-style beef brisket dinner(makes about 8 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan, add onion recipe soup mix blended with water.
Add brisket, turning to coat with soup mixture.
Loosely wrap with aluminum foil and roast 1 hour.
Add potatoes and carrots; toss to coat with soup mixture.
Reseal foil and continue roasting 2 hours or until brisket and vegetables are tender.
Thicken gravy if desired.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: orange pineapple freeze
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill well.
Continue as normal for hand or electric ice cream freezer.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil with garlic.
Stir in onion soup, water, tomato paste and sauce, salt, oregano and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Rinse with cold water.
Arrange alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese in a casserole.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or 350° for 30 minutes or until Mozzarella is melted.
Yields 6 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix coconut and pecans.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour on coconut and pecans.
In saucepan, heat margarine and cream cheese until mixture is warm enough to stir in confectioners sugar.
Spoon on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't cut until it is cold.

title: patty shells
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into shells.
Bake at 325° to 350° until brown.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream together vegetable shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add small amount at a time to creamed mixture, alternating with the 1/4 cup milk.
Mix well. Add vanilla and undrained pineapple.
Blend well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours or until done to the touch.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and pour icing over while still hot.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Combine in container with lid and shake vigorously.
Keeps about 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Beat potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and garlic at high speed until smooth.
Stir in chives.
Spoon into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon paprika.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snow ball cookies
directions: Mix oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Refrigerate, chill, shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Shake gently in paper bag with powdered sugar.
Store in closed container.

title: peggy's macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Bake pie shell (or use graham cracker crust).
Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Press all but a little of this mixture into pie shell.
Make pudding by instructions on box.
Pour into shell.
Let set.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remainder of powdered sugar and peanut butter on top.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs.
Meanwhile, in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook celery and onion until tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir undiluted soup, milk, and mayonnaise into vegetables in saucepan.
Drain noodles; add, with tuna and tomato chunks, to saucepan and toss to coat.
Spoon mixture into deep 2-quart casserole.
In 1-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Tear bread into small pieces and toss with melted butter.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over noodle mixture.
Bake casserole 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash and pick fresh blueberries or thaw and drain frozen blueberries.

title: wonder cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pull apart garlic bread
directions: Cut the 2 frozen dough into 96 pieces. Mix the next 5 ingredients together (not the bread dough). Dip bread dough into egg mixture; drop into an angel food or Bundt pan. Let rise overnight. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Pour mixture over potatoes and toss to coat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Stir occasionally to absorb liquid.

title: chicken divan
directions: Lay broccoli in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Place chicken pieces on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry and mix well.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with cheese. Combine bread crumbs and melted oleo and sprinkle over top.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes.
This serves 6.
Fluffy rice is an excellent accompaniment.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Cook sugar, milk and cocoa 1 minute.
Cool and add margarine and vanilla and beat until spreading consistency.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add juice to vanilla pudding mix; mix well. Add pineapple chunks, fruit cocktail and bananas.
If more liquid is needed, add some fruit cocktail juice.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and serve with assorted crackers.

title: spanish cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in pan that has been greased and dusted
with corn meal.
Bake in oven at 425° until brown.

title: "no peek" chicken
directions: Mix together and place on bottom of buttered pan.
Place raw chicken pieces on top, any number can be used.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 350° or until done.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Throw together the butter or margarine and flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add mushroom soup, mushrooms and cheese; mix until smooth.
Add 2 tablespoons or more of cooking sherry.
Add shrimp or lobster; sprinkle with parsley.
Add a dash of garlic powder. Serve on hot rice or pastry shells.
Simple and excellent.

title: oregon clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion in large kettle.
Drain seafood; add liquid, potatoes and water to onion and bacon.
Cook until potatoes are tender, 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add seafood, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: layered cauliflower salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and cut flowerets in bite-size pieces.
Layer lettuce, onions, cauliflowerets and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar well.
Spread over top to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese; then cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight and toss gently before serving.
Serves 8.

title: falafil or taamiyah(lebanese; international)
directions: Mix all ingredients very well and knead well. Let it stand, covered, for 2 1/2 hours. Let the oil get hot on high heat. Add a dash of baking soda to the falafil with tablespoon water. Mix well. Shape into small circles; pat with the palm of your hands, then fry in oil for 3 minutes on each side or until brown. Drain. Serve with pita bread, chopped parsley, pickles, tahini, chopped tomatoes.

title: bacon mushroom roll-ups
directions: Cook bacon first.
In large skillet, saute bacon, mushrooms, onion, salt and pepper for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in cream cheese; set aside.
Cut crust off of bread and roll bread with rolling pin to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread about 2 tablespoons of mixture over each slice of bread.
Roll and use toothpick to hold in place. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Cut into 1-inch bites.
Place on cookie sheet.
Brush with butter.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes!

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Start counting the time when margarine is melted and starts to boil. Let boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter (crunchy or smooth).
Beat until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and continue to beat until light.
Add vanilla and sifted flour.
Mix well and fold in chopped nuts. Shape into small balls on an ungreased baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for 15 to 18 minutes, until light, light brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill square baking dish with sliced apples.
Mix together the ingredients and spread over apples.
Melt butter and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Prepare noodles. Combine corned beef, mushroom soup and milk. Mix with noodles.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pineapple goody(yields 16 servings)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 325° for glass dish and at 350° for metal pan.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Lay peaches on brown sugar mixture.
Pour batter over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Place cake mix and pudding in a large bowl.
Add eggs, oil, boiling water and poppy seed.
Place in 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
This bread freezes well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Oil potatoes lightly and bake at 350° until soft.
Peel. Cream potatoes; remove strings (fibers).
Add other ingredients. Blend until smooth.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best if topped before baking.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, milk, butter and cocoa into pan.
Bring to a boil until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Let stand 1/2 hour until dry.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: ken's morning salad
directions: Add pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and bananas to instant pudding.
Chill.
A great brunch salad when fresh fruit is not in season.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick and easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Slice into a large bowl.
Add sugar and oil. Stir occasionally until sugar dissolves.
Rinse jar and return pickles and syrup to jar.
Refrigerate until crisp (about 2 days).

title: breadsticks italiano
directions: Combine all ingredients except breadsticks; mix well.
Place dough on cookie sheet according to package directions.
Spread lightly with margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with remaining margarine mixture. Makes 8 breadsticks.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: In baking dish, break up bread slices.
Brown sausage slightly, drain.
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over bread and sausage.
Beat eggs; add milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over mixture.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add onion and tomatoes; simmer 10 minutes.
Blend cream and flour and add along with sherry, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and paprika to taste.
Add shrimp and put in large buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake in 350° oven until brown, 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spice chiffon cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and cloves.
Set aside.
In another bowl, whip egg whites and cream of tartar until a very stiff peak forms.
Set aside.
To the dry ingredients, add oil, water, vanilla and egg yolks.
Mix until smooth.
Pour egg whites into yolk mixture, gently folding with rubber scraper until blended.
Bake in 10-inch ungreased tube pan at 325° for 55 minutes.
Towards last heat at 350° until done.
Invert, let cool.
Stays moist.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover, chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with tines of fork dipped in granulated sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Store tightly covered. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: one meal dish
directions: Scramble sausage in a large skillet and cook almost done. Chop green peppers and onions; cook until done.
Add corn, diced tomatoes, Mrs. Dash seasoning and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Best served with cornbread.

title: vegetables parmigiana
directions: Seed pepper and cut into chunks.
Set aside.
Heat oil; add eggplant, zucchini, peppers and onions.
Cook until barely tender. Drain vegetables on paper toweling.

title: cream rhubarb pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, milk and flour. Fold in diced rhubarb. Put into pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
