Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Chopped onion can also be added.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook ground beef and 1/2 cup onions in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir baking mix, milk and eggs until blended.
Pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining onions. Bake 25 to 27 minutes or until crust is light brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: montezumos revenge(rocky's chili)
directions: Cook onions, garlic, bell pepper and hot peppers in beer while meat is browning.
After the meat is browned, add vegetables and spices and tomato sauce and cook slowly for about 2 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Put in greased baking dish in order given.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In separate bowl, beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add 2 cups sugar, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well blended.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place balls 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Flatten lightly with bottom of a drinking glass.
Bake 8 minutes or until golden.
Makes 66.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring the sugar and milk to a boil in a heavy saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add the peanut butter and marshmallow cream and mix well.
Pour immediately into a buttered 8 x 8-inch dish. Chill until set.
Cut into small squares.
Yield: 3 to 4 dozen.

title: hot mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon; heat in a chafing dish or double boiler.
Top with crisp bacon, crumbled.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.
Makes 3 cups.

title: ragoux
directions: Put heat on medium low and add onion, margarine and cloves. When onions are golden brown, add chicken (skin can be removed before frying).
While chicken is browning, make your meatballs. Roll meatballs in flour and brown in pan.
Drain meatballs on paper towels.
When chicken is golden brown, add just enough water to cover the chicken.
Add the chicken cubes.
Put heat to medium high until water boils for 5 minutes, then put down to medium low. Make sure water doesn't evaporate.
Once meatballs are browned and drained, add to the ingredients in the pot.
Add water as needed.
Cook for 3 hours.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Cut butter into flour mixture.
Thoroughly mix in buttermilk.
Add raisins and caraway seeds.
Knead dough lightly and form into a flat, round loaf.
Place in a greased and lightly-floured cake tin.
(If you have a cast-iron skillet, this is best!)
Cut a cross in the top of the loaf about 1/2 inch deep.

title: cherry-coconut bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and confectioners sugar until smooth. Spread thin with the fingers in an 8 or 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and spread over the top of the baked pastry. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: tomato barbecued chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 2 tablespoons fat.
Place in casserole.
To the drippings in the pan, add celery and onion.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by small teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 13 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs; mix together egg yolks and milk.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.

title: texas hash
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; drain off grease.
Place in crock-pot and add rice, chopped onions, green pepper, salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, mushrooms, crushed tomatoes and almost all of tomato juice.
Mix well and turn crock-pot on high.
It will be ready to eat in about 4 hours.
This makes a good Sunday dinner.

title: lite and zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can of onions around and under chicken. Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; top with remaining onions.
Bake 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.
(I usually double the recipe.)

title: pudding stripe cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package.
Bake in 13 X 9 inch baking pan.
poke holes at once down in cake
with wooden spoon 1 inch apart.
After holes are made, combine pudding mix with sugar in bowl.
Stir in milk.
Beat on low for 1 minute.
Quickly before pudding thickens, pour 1/2
of pudding mixture over cake and into holes to make stripes.
Allow pudding to thicken slightly.
Spoon over the top.
Swirl to frost cake.
Chill 1 hour.

title: cornbread
directions: Blend onion, jalapeno pepper, oil and eggs in blender.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add tomato paste, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Heat milk and cream cheese over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, green pepper, garlic salt and noodles.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of noodle mixture and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese when serving.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add and mix all other ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dieter's snack
directions: Break broccoli into flowerets.
Cut off ends of stems and cut up stems.
In a jar, pour mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Shake until blended.
Pour over broccoli.
Mix in sunflower seeds, raisins and crumbled bacon. Can be stored in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt
oleo and chips. Cool.
Pour over marshmallows and nuts. Form in rolls. Roll in coconut.

title: graham cracker muffins
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar, salt and butter.
Pour hot milk over mixture and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spoon mixture into greased small muffin pans, filling them two-thirds full.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for twenty minutes.

title: oven fried chicken with buttermilk gravy
directions: In a shallow dish, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika; set aside.
Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels. Brush chicken with melted margarine.
If desired, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip chicken into crumb mixture, turning to coat. Arrange chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until tender and no longer pink.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Clean and cut chicken in desired size.
Put in a medium size pot.
Combine ingredients together.
Cook on medium heat.
Simmer until done.

title: pesto
directions: Put the basil, olive oil, pine nuts, garlic cloves and salt in the blender; mix at high speed.
Stop from time to time and scrape the ingredients down toward the bottom of the blender with a rubber spatula.
When the ingredients are evenly blended, pour in the cheeses and blend until the mixture is smooth.
If pesto is too thick, add to it a tablespoon or so of the hot water in which the pasta has boiled.
Pour the pesto sauce over your favorite hot pasta.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar.
Add the well beaten eggs.
Sift the dry ingredients and blend the entire mixture.
Spread thin in a greased pan.
Bake at 400° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet hot pickles
directions: Drain pickles; discard juice.
Place all ingredients in a large crock or Pyrex bowl.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Let sit 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Return to jar.
Turn jar upside down every day for 5 days.
Good for gift giving.

title: saturday night spread
directions: Brown meat and onion; add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve on sandwich buns while hot.

title: diet salad
directions: Mix fruit, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Sprinkle jello a little at a time.
Mix well, then refrigerate.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, cake mix and pudding.
Stir 7-Up in by hand.

title: shipwreck
directions: Butter an oblong baking dish and add the first 5 ingredients. Over this mixture, pour tomato soup and kidney beans.
Cover the entire mixture with chili powder to taste.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat eggs, Wesson oil and sugar together.
Add flour, soda, salt and fruit cocktail.
Mix well and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: firecracker chili stew
directions: Brown the beef cubes in bacon drippings for about 5 minutes. Combine browned beef, bacon and remaining ingredients in a slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or until beef is tender.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and slowly add brown sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture mixing well.
Stir in oats, cereal and nuts.
(Dough will be stiff.) Drop by teaspoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cook on wire rack.
Yields: 7 dozen.

title: chocolate sandwich cookies
directions: Mix together in order as given; beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake seven minutes at 400°.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale when serving.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and cheese; gradually add sugar and cream until shiny.
Add flour and eggs alternately, beating after each addition; add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Quarter the cabbage and cover with water.
Add carrots and cook until half done.
Next, add turnips, potatoes, onion and Polish sausage and cook until tender.
Salt to taste.
Serve with corn bread.
Serves 8.

title: butter rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients to make into biscuit type batter. Roll out onto lightly floured surface.
Roll to thin crust. Spread softened margarine on top of crust.
Sprinkle sugar all over butter.
Roll up crust like a jelly roll.
Slice into 4-inch rolls and place into deep baking dish.
Cover with water and add vanilla.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until top is brown.
Water will be a thick syrup.

title: turtles
directions: Lightly oil large baking sheet or cookie tin.
Arrange 60 groups of cashew nuts, 4 to each group.
Allow caramel syrup to cool slightly in pan, but be sure it is still liquid.
Spoon tablespoon of liquid caramel over cashew nuts.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon melted chocolate over top of each caramel turtle. Allow to cool completely until quite firm.
Yields 60 turtles.

title: easy chicken cordon blue
directions: Pound chicken
breast
until
flat.
Put 1 slice of ham and 1 slice
of
Swiss cheese on top and roll up.
Secure with toothpick.	Chill for at least 1 hour.
Roll chicken in flour, then egg, then bread crumbs.
Place in a baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and honey.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange rhubarb pieces in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over top.
Sprinkle with sugar and then cake mix.
Drizzle butter over top, followed by cold water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve topped with whipped cream or frozen whipped topping.

title: bobbie's pie crust(for 9 or 10-inch pie)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Blend in lard with pastry blender.
Add water slowly, tossing with fork until clingy, then roll together with fingers until it forms a ball.
Divide in two for top and bottom crust.
Roll out on pastry cloth with a little whole wheat flour or wheat bran to keep from sticking.

title: zippy pasta
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Add onions, green pepper, Salad Supreme, garlic and half of dressing.
Refrigerate overnight. Just before serving, add rest of dressing.

title: chocolate angel icebox cake
directions: Cut the cake into 3 to 4 equal pieces.
Cream together the butter and 2 1/2 cups powdered sugar until light.
Blend in the egg yolks, melted chocolate and milk with the rum and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread the filling between the layers of the cake.
Whip cream until stiff.
Flavor with the 2 tablespoons powdered sugar and the remaining vanilla.
Frost top and sides of the cake with the whipped cream.
Chill for 2 to 4 hours.
Sprinkle with cocoa. Garnish with orange slices or berries if desired.

title: sausage roll
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Mix sausage, green pepper, egg and seasonings in bowl.
Roll out 2 rectangles of dough to about 8 x 10-inch size.
Spread all of mixture on top of both rolls, almost to edges.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese on top of both rolls and roll up lengthwise.
Brush on egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kolacky
directions: Cut lard into half the flour.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in milk.
Add beaten eggs to yeast mixture.
Gradually add liquids to dry mixture (lard and flour), alternating with remaining flour. Knead in bowl (dough will be very sticky).
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour and beat steak.
Salt and pepper.
Brown in a small amount of oil on both sides.
Place in large pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cook on top of stove on low heat for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours until tender.

title: scalloped potatoes and franks
directions: Cook potatoes and onions with salt in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.
Slice franks.
Mix potatoes, onions, franks, flour, salt, butter, 1 can of Hunt's sauce, cheese and parsley together.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour remaining can of Hunt's sauce over. Bake 35 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans.
Optionally, soak them overnight.
Put all ingredients in a large pot and add enough water to cover twice. Bring to a boil and lower heat to simmer.
Cover pot and cook about 3 hours until beans are soft.
Add oil and cook another 1/2 hour.
Serve over steamed rice with plenty of butter and French bread.
Serves 6.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine lettuce, onions, beans and cheese.
Mix well and chill.
Before serving, add Fritos and dressing.

title: hobo dinner
directions: You will also need a large piece of heavy-duty foil.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Gradually add sugar to well beaten eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with oil and sour cream, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, apples and pecans.

title: beef broccoli pie
directions: In a medium skillet, brown beef and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add 1 1/4 cups milk and softened cream cheese.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Add a moderate amount of the hot creamed mixture to the skillet and cook over medium heat until mixture is thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cooked broccoli; set aside.
Line a 9-inch pan with pie shell.
Cut Monterey Jack cheese into slices.
Arrange slices on top of meat mixture.
Adjust the top crust and put small amount of milk around on top crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
If the pastry browns too quickly, cover edge with foil during last 10 minutes. Let pie stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add powdered sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add in vanilla.
Stir in pecans, if desired or reserve them to sprinkle over top of frosted cake.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together, except the eggs and onion. Blend the eggs and onion in a blender, then add to the other mixture.
Bake in a greased or buttered pie dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: forgotten roast
directions: Place roast on large piece of tinfoil and arrange vegetables (enough for your family) around roast.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Spoon undiluted soup on top.
Wrap loosely with foil, making sure it's sealed at the top and sides.
Place in roaster pan.
Bake at 275° for 3 to 4 hours.
Excellent with deer meat also.

title: waldorf-style salad
directions: In small mixing bowl, sprinkle lemon juice over apples and toss lightly to combine; add celery, raisins and mayonnaise and mix until thoroughly coated.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add the tea bags; steep for 6 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Add whole chives and cinnamon.
Leave spices in 30 minutes, then remove.
Add jello, cranberry juice, apple juice, frozen orange juice and lemon juice.
Will keep for several weeks. Heat and serve.

title: ma eva's tea cakes
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and mix good.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll out and cut. Bake at 350° until brown.
tags: baking powder for each c. of flour

title: pesto deviled eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise, scoop out yolks and place them in small bowl; set aside egg white halves.
Add pesto and mayonnaise to yolks and stir until smooth.
Spoon mixture into halved egg whites.
Garnish each with a parsley leaf.
Makes 12 halves.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub and rinse potatoes.
Cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish and fan out slightly.
Sprinkle on salt; drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle on herbs.
Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for another 10 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut for 15 minutes.
Place in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well. Stir together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° to 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves, 9 x 5 x 2-inches.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Layer cookies and bananas on bottom of large bowl.
Add 1/2 of mixture.
Repeat. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill, then serve.
Makes a lot!
Great for a large crowd.

title: mr. nik's chocolate chunk cheese cake
directions: Melt butter and combine with 1/3 cup sugar and crumbs.
Press into bottom of 9-inch or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Heat in oven at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spread pineapple evenly in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread pie filling on top. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of pie filling, sprinkling nuts over top of that, if desired. Cut butter in slices and place across top. Bake for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a covered dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Remove and sprinkle with grated sharp or American cheese. Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place sugar, oil and pumpkin in a large bowl.
Beat well at a medium speed.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat well after each one.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in batter and add nuts.
Bake one hour.

title: g.p.'s hobo bread
directions: Bring coffee to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add baking soda and raisins.
Cover and let sit overnight.
The next morning, add white and brown sugar, nuts, flour and salt.
Mix well.
Grease and flour 3 one pound coffee tins.
Divide batter evenly between the three cans.
(Slightly more than half full.)
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 65 minutes.
Cool in cans for 15 minutes before removing.
If necessary, tap cans on bottom to release loaf.
Turn loaf on side and slice into rounds for serving.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: aunt mimi's tomato relish
directions: Put vegetables through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook over low flame for 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: lemon broiled rainbow trout
directions: Place fish fillets on lightly greased broiler pan, skin side down.
Brush fillets with melted margarine.
Sprinkle approximately 1/2 tablespoon Old Bay Dash O'Lemon seasoning blend over each fillet.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes or until fish flakes easily. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: delicious iced tea
directions: Bring the
water and sugar to a boil.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spray a large casserole with vegetable cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Fry the ground beef until just about done.
Add onions and cook until onions are transparent.
Drain and set aside.
In large bowl, melt the Velveeta cheese in the microwave.
When melted where you can stir, add the ground beef, onions, picante sauce and chili.
Continue to heat until mixed well.
Best if served hot with tortilla chips. If mixture becomes too thick, you can add a little milk to thin.
This makes a large amount.

title: kraut
directions: Put vinegar and salt in saucepan and boil until dissolved. You can add some water from the gallon to the vinegar and salt to help get dissolved.
When salt is dissolved, add this to the remaining gallon of water.
Pack sterilized jars with chopped cabbage and cover with solution, leaving 1/2-inch of space at the top of the jars.
Put caps on jars and store in cool, dry place.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Place all ingredients except water in blender.	Process until smooth.
Combine
strawberry
puree with water in saucepan; heat slowly until
hot.	Serve
warm
or
chill and serve cold.	Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty ingredients into a 9 x 12-inch cake pan in the order listed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Cook squash, in small amount of boiling, salted water, for about 10 to 15 minutes, until barely tender.
Drain and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds.
Arrange the shells in a greased shallow baking dish.

title: orange julius
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until ice is well crushed.
Enjoy!

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook ground meat and drain off excess fat.
Saute onion until limp.
Add chicken soup and rice to boiling water and cook for 7 minutes.
Add all ingredients together and bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water and 1/4 slice of the ice cream.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
When firm, layer with thin layer of sour cream.
Continue with next flavor, doing the same thing.
Each layer should have a thin layer of sour cream, finishing with sour cream or whipped cream on top.
First layer will take longest to get firm, but next 3 go faster.
When it's finished, it looks like a colorful ribbon.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until soft; drain. Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pastor groover's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and simmer over low heat until onions are tender.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: michiko's salmon
directions: Sprinkle Hawaiian salt on salmon and let stand.
Melt butter and saute garlic.
Add salmon and saute on both sides.
Smother oyster sauce and mayonnaise on salmon.
Add onion on the side of pan and stir-fry.
Pour some onion on top of salmon.
Cover and cook on slow heat until salmon is done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt margarine. Add sugars and mix well. Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla and cream. Add flour, salt and soda; mix. Add chocolate chips. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peeto's brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, shortening, eggs and vanilla; beat.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in 8 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: melt in your mouth sugar cookie
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, tartar, soda, almond flavoring and oil.
Add flour gradually.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peaches 'n cream
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla pudding in large bowl. Beat 2 minutes. Pour into greased square pan. Place peach slices over batter in pan.

title: party potatoes
directions: Beat sour cream and cream cheese until blended; add to hot potatoes, beating until light and fluffy.
If too stiff, add a little milk.
Season to taste with garlic salt.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine; sprinkle with paprika and brown.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Heat in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereals, pretzel sticks and nuts in ovenproof pan.
Blend butter and seasoning; pour over cereal mixture.
Stir well.
Bake 30 minutes.
Stir once or twice. Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: cream cheese roll-overs
directions: Stir olives into cream cheese.
Spread on flour tortillas. Sprinkle with seasoning of choice.
Roll up and slice into 1-inch slices.
Put into fridge until ready to serve.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Cream together Ricotta and cream cheese.
Add flour, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla, beating well.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, using low speed of mixer.
Gently mix in sour cream, then pour mixture into the pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off, leave in oven for 3 to 5 hours.
Remove from oven, top with any kind of pie filling.
Cook 2 days before serving.

title: milkless-eggless-butterless cake
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients together for 5 minutes.
When cold, add soda which has been dissolved in a little warm water.
Add the flour.
Mix well and bake in a loaf pan or large baking pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix chopped cabbage, onion, pepper and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Can be stored in refrigerator for days.

title: shrimp and chicken
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook onion, margarine and garlic until tender.
With slotted spoon, remove mixture to bowl.
Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
In same skillet, cook chicken until golden on all sides.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, 3 tablespoons parsley, basil and onion mixture.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; heat to boiling and simmer until shrimp are pink and tender. Sprinkle with parsley.
Can be served over rice.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onions and simmer until golden brown.
Add ground beef.
Stir with a fork while onions brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake in hot 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fruit drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and fruit.
Combine dry ingredients and add slowly, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Use ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will swell slightly as baking.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cool slightly, about 5 minutes.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: white bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt, milk and oil.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a dough you can handle.
Knead on floured board until smooth; place in oiled bowl, turn one time to oil top and let rise 1 hour in warm place.
Punch down and knead for about 5 minutes.
Shape into 2 loaves; let rise until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes.
Brush top with butter; let stand 10 minutes before turning out on rack to cool.

title: hello dollys
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix graham cracker crumbs into melted butter.
Place layer of coconut, then layer of chocolate chips, then layer of nuts.
Spread Eagle Brand milk over this and bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: delicious meat loaf(salpicon al queso)
directions: Place bread in small dish.
Add hot evaporated milk.
Use fork to crumble soaked bread.
Set aside.
Heat oil in medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and garlic. Saute until tender, about 5 minute, stirring often to prevent burning.
Place meat in large mixing bowl.
Add sauteed onion mixture but do not mix.
Froth egg yolks with fork and add to meat along with tomato sauce, hot sauce, cheese, parsley, salt and 2 tablespoons seasoned bread crumbs.
Use wooden spoons to mix lightly and thoroughly.
Add soaked bread.
Mix again.
Whip egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into meat mixture.
Place long piece of wax paper on work surface and spread remaining bread crumbs down middle.
Place meat mixture on crumbs.
Gently mold into loaf about 14 x 4-inches.
Do not handle meat too much and do not press meat mixture firmly together.
Pull up sides of paper to coat meat loaf with crumbs.
Gently roll meat loaf onto greased pan, placing at angle if necessary to fit.
Sprinkle any remaining crumbs evenly over surface.
Bake on center rack of 325° oven, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Pour Onion Topping over.
Bake 40 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Serve hot, cut into slices.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rosie's lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasonings, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook lasagna noodles in salted water for 10 to 13 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; pour cold water over them until they are cool enough to handle.
Combine cottage cheese and egg.
Place 1/2 of noodles in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of meat sauce over noodles, then 1/2 of the cottage cheese mixture, then 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese slices and sprinkle with 1/2 of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: supreme cranberry sauce
directions: Grind or process cranberries and orange (with rind).
Combine. Mix Jell-O and sugar with water.
Combine Jell-O with fruit.
Add nuts.
Chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread evenly in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 cup water over apples.
Then top with 1 1/4 cups of flour, 2/3 cup sugar and 1/2 cup margarine.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Seed peppers and grind or chop.
Mix pepper with sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil for 6 minutes, then add Certo.
Prepare jars and lids for jelly.
Pour into jelly glasses and cap.
Wear gloves while preparing hot pepper.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat broiler. Mix mayo, juice and seasoning. Place chicken on broiler pan; brush with 1/2 of mixture. Broil 5 minutes; turn, then brush remaining mixture. Broil 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fish cake pupus
directions: Slice cucumber lengthwise and remove seeds.
Put crab sticks inside cucumber and place halves together.
Spread mayonnaise on one side of the Chikuwa and push cucumber through.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and serve with shoyu or mustard/shoyu sauce.

title: german slaw
directions: Arrange cabbage and onions in bowl.
Bring to a boil, sugar, celery, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add oil; pour over cabbage and onions.
Chill for several hours.
This slaw will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: aunt donna's vermont beef stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cook at 250° for 6 to 8 hours, covered. Last 20 minutes, add 1 package frozen peas.
Cook uncovered.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in dish (Pyrex type).
Mix flour, sugar, eggs and milk; stir in corn.
Pour into dish with melted margarine. Bake 30 minutes (per can) at 350°.
(If recipe is doubled, bake one hour.)

title: italian bow-knot cookies
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Stir
in the sugar and baking powder. In a separate bowl, beat eggs with milk and extracts.
Add egg mixture to the flour mixture.
Stir until mixed and turn onto a floured board and knead for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate for 1 hour. Cut off small pieces of dough; roll pencil thin 6 inches long. Twist into a loose knot.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: perfect microwave bran muffins
directions: Combine bran, flour, baking soda, salt and raisins in a large bowl.
In another bowl combine egg, yogurt, molasses and honey. Stir egg mixture
into
bran mixture along with melted butter. Stir in walnuts.
Fill
paper-lined
muffin
cups 2/3 full. Microwave 6 at a time for
to 3 minutes on High power. Yields 14 to 16 muffins.

title: creamy pumpkin dessert
directions: Slice cookie dough thin and place on bottom, sides and corners of 13 x 9-inch pan (do not grease or flour).
Pack way up.
Cream the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla until smooth. Pour on top of cookie dough.
Mix together the 1 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 4 eggs and spice, then add pumpkin and evaporated milk.
Mix well and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 370° for 45 to 55 minutes or until a toothpick can be inserted into center, dry.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion and garlic in hot oil.
Add meat.
Cook until browned.
Blend tomatoes, taco seasoning and chilies.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain fat.

title: taboli
directions: Soak wheat in 2 cups lukewarm water while preparing other ingredients. After chopping all ingredients, drain excess water from heat.
Combine all ingredients, cover and allow to set overnight. Stir again before serving.
This will serve about 10 to 12.

title: orange cream cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions for a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hamburg.
Brown hamburg while sauce is simmering.
Drain hamburg.
Put into sauce.
Simmer at least 1 hour.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Blend together flour and sugar.
Melt margarine; add Coca-Cola, oil, cocoa and marshmallows in saucepan over low heat. Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Wash and grind cranberries.
Add sugar.
Drain in colander in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, cut red grapes in halves.
Cut up pecans.
Whip cream gradually.
Add 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in cranberries.
Add other ingredients.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer
5 minutes.
Unroll dough and press on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan. Prick bottom and sides.
Bake 12 minutes.
Cover crust with meat mixture and top with cheese and bake until melted.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and olives.
I put sour cream in the middle also.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; stir in beans.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft.
Slowly beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; stir in chips a little at a time.
Put in pie crust and chill for 4 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to the egg mixture; stir until well blended. Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
